text: Chomo Lonzo is a mountain in the Himalayas range, in Tibet. It has three different summits. These are the main (or South) peak (), central peak (), and North peak (). It is the 24th highest mountain in the world. The first people to reach the top of the main peak were Jean Couzy and Lionel Terray, in 1954. ==References== Category:Himalayas Category:Mountains of Tibet
